			<strong><a class="nav" href="eyestorm-list.htm" target="_self">eyestorm</a></strong> 
			<br>
			<strong><a class="nav" href="catalogues-list.htm" target="_self">catalogues</a></strong> 
			<br>
			<br>
			<strong><a class="nav" href="search.htm" target="_self">search</a></strong> 
			<br>
		</td>
		<td width="400" align="left" valign="top">
			<h1 class="exhibition">Introduction</h1> 
			<p>
				&nbsp; 
			</p>
			<p>
				I have worked as an art critic in London since 1994, writing over 100 articles for various magazines and exhibition catalogues. I am now collating those articles on this website. 
			</p>
			<p>
				To view the articles, simply select a publication from the set of links on the left, then choose an article from the list that follows. Only those articles whose titles appear in red have been added to the site so far - apologies for the gaps, but I am adding more as I get the time. 
			</p>
<!--
			<p>
				Latest additions (added October 2006): 
				<br>
				<a href="artmonthly/am-east06.htm">East International 2006</a>, Art Monthly, 2006 
				<br>
			</p>
			<br>
			-->
<!--
			<p>
				<strong>Contemporary Art at Tate Modern</strong>
				<br>
				In October 2005 I will be teaching an evening course entitled 'Contemporary Art at Tate Modern' at the City University in London. To find out more or to enrol, view the <a href="http://www.city.ac.uk/conted/cfa/arts/artdesign/ce1686.html" target="_blank">course details on the University's website</a>. 
			</p>
			<br>
			-->
			<p>
				<strong>The 'New Art Up-Close' Book Series</strong> 
				<br>
				My books, on Gary Hume, Gavin Turk, and Jake and Dinos Chapman, are available now. To find out more or order them online, visit the series website: <a href="http://www.newartupclose.com/">www.newartupclose.com</a>. 
			</p>
			<br>
			<p>
				Website by Royal Jelly Factory 
				<br>
				<a href="http://www.royaljellyfactory.com">www.royaljellyfactory.com</a> 
			</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>
			&nbsp; 
		</td>
		<td align="left" valign="top">
			<br>
