  <!-- Begin .post -->
  <div class="post"><a name="1750122018131180805"></a>
         
    <h3 class="post-title">
	 
	 Museums obviously can't do math
	 
    </h3>
    

	         <div class="post-body">
	<div>
      Howdy!<br /><br />There's all sorts of bafflegab and gobbledy-gook happening in <a href="http://www.newswire.ca/en/releases/archive/May2007/27/c5558.html">this press release</a> about yesterday's <a href="http://www.museesmontreal.org/site/museumsday.htm">Montreal Museum's Day</a>. Nowhere can I find any <a href="http://www.museesmontreal.org/site/mtmain28f1.htm">press release</a> or other sort of factual documentation about attendance at the JournÃ©e des musÃ©es montrÃ©alais in 2006 which is sort of surprising since it was the 20th anniversary. But I scratch my head when last week they released <a href="http://zekesgallery.blogspot.com/2007/05/mario-cloutier-doesnt-fact-check.html">something that ostensibly showed how 125,000 people participated in 2006</a>, and then this year they state that they "<span style="font-style: italic;">maintained last year's attendance once again</span>" but they only got 108,000 people. A 14% drop in attendance isn't maintaining anything.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.canada.com/montrealgazette/news/montreal/story.html?id=c36b906c-5d98-4a77-8f00-4bb52cef2357">This article by Cheryl Cornacchia in the Montreal Gazette</a> does a better job of analyzing the results. <a href="http://www.ledevoir.com/2007/05/28/145085.html">Le Devoir on the other hand doesn't let the facts get in the way of a photo op</a>.
    </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Begin Feedburner FeedFlare -->
    <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;font-size:78%;font-family: arial;"><script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/blogspot/wjBk?i=http://www.zekesgallery.blogspot.in/2007/05/museums-obviously-cant-do-math.html" type="text/javascript"></script></script></span>
    <!-- End Feedburner FeedFlare -->

    <p class="post-footer">
