    <h3 class="post-title">
	 
	 Rafael Lozano-Hemmer vs. David Altmejd. The Montrealers at Venice
	 
    </h3>
    

	         <div class="post-body">
	<div>
      Howdy!<br /><br />I just set up a <a href="http://news.google.com/news?ie=utf8&amp;oe=utf8&amp;q=Lozano-Hemmer+OR+Altmejd&amp;hl=en">Google News Alert</a> to track who gets more internet press in English, Rafael Lozano-Hemmer or David Altmejd. <a href="http://news.google.com/news?ie=utf8&amp;oe=utf8&amp;q=Lozano-Hemmer+OR+Altmejd&amp;hl=en">Right now</a> there are <a href="http://news.google.com/news?um=1&tab=wn&ie=UTF-8&lr=&oe=UTF-8&q=Altmejd">nine for Altmejd</a> and <a href="http://news.google.com/news?um=1&tab=wn&ie=UTF-8&lr=&oe=UTF-8&q=Lozano-Hemmer&btnG=Search+News">five for Lozano-Hemmer</a>. For comparison purposes <a href="http://news.google.com/news?um=1&tab=wn&ie=UTF-8&lr=&oe=UTF-8&q=Gonzalez-Torres">Felix Gonzalez-Torres (the dead American artist at Venice this year) has 13</a>.
    </div>
    </div>

