  <div class="post"><a name="5186649879019211334"></a>
         
    <h3 class="post-title">
	 
	 Galerie Concorde is hiring again
	 
    </h3>
    

	         <div class="post-body">
	<div>
      Howdy!<br /><br />If as they state in <a href="http://workingmontrealjobs.canada.com/texis/jobsearch/details.html?id=4651474849b520">this advertisement</a> that they pay $125,000 (which is I assume per year) I do not understand why they have such difficulty in retaining employees. The previous job advertisements that I've seen are from <a href="http://zekesgallery.blogspot.com/2006/05/need-job.html">May 2006</a>, <a href="http://zekesgallery.blogspot.com/2007/02/galerie-concorde-seems-to-be-getting.html">February 16, 2007</a> and <a href="http://zekesgallery.blogspot.com/2007/02/galerie-concorde-is-now-fast-paced-art.html">February 25, 2007</a>. Or maybe they are <a href="http://www.azcentral.com/arizonarepublic/news/articles/0408artworks0408.html">thinking of selling art on cruise ships like Park West Galleries</a> and need to hire more staff because of that.
    </div>
    </div>

