  <div class="post"><a name="671609025639078564"></a>
         
    <h3 class="post-title">
	 
	 Props and Shout Outs to Lisa Hunter
	 
    </h3>
    

	         <div class="post-body">
	<div>
      Howdy!<br /><br />She is the subject of <a href="http://www.canada.com/components/print.aspx?id=ffefd615-f6a4-44b3-bcfc-306fe455fbaa">a very nice article in today's Montreal Gazette</a>. It also comes with a large and flattering photo. <br /><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://www.canada.com/components/print.aspx?id=ffefd615-f6a4-44b3-bcfc-306fe455fbaa"><img style="cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px;" src="http://a123.g.akamai.net/f/123/12465/1d/media.canada.com/idl/mtgz/20070521/13649-5348.jpg" border="0" alt="" /></a><br /><br />And as a <span style="font-style:italic;">web exclusive</span> the Gazette has<a href="http://www.canada.com/montrealgazette/news/story.html?id=1786def1-a359-4250-bd73-edfbb170673f"> a resource section on art in Montreal</a> - which somehow missed mentioning the <a href="http://zekesgallery.blogspot.com/2007/05/internet-news-on-biennale.html">Biennale de Montreal</a>.<br /><br />If you're interested in reading <a href="http://howtobuyart.blogspot.com/">The Intrepid Art Collector</a>, Ms. Hunter's blog click on <a href="http://howtobuyart.blogspot.com/">the appropriate link</a>. Or if you want to buy <a href="http://www.amazon.ca/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.ca%2FIntrepid-Art-Collector-Beginners-Appreciating%2Fdp%2F0307237133%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1174425869%26sr%3D1-1&tag=zekesgaller0f-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=15121&creative=330641">Ms. Hunter's book</a> try either of these links:<br /><br /><iframe src="http://rcm.amazon.com/e/cm?t=zekesgallery-20&o=1&amp;p=8&l=as1&amp;asins=0307237133&fc1=000000&amp;IS2=1&lt1=_blank&amp;amp;amp;lc1=0000FF&bc1=000000&amp;bg1=FFFFFF&f=ifr" style="width: 120px; height: 240px;" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe> or <iframe src="http://rcm-ca.amazon.ca/e/cm?t=zekesgaller0f-20&o=15&amp;p=8&l=as1&amp;asins=0307237133&fc1=000000&amp;IS2=1&lt1=_blank&amp;amp;amp;lc1=0000FF&bc1=000000&amp;bg1=FFFFFF&f=ifr" style="width: 120px; height: 240px;" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe><br /><br />And then if you want to read my review of it before you buy, <a href="http://zekesgallery.blogspot.com/2007/03/zekes-gallery-book-review-intrepid-art.html">click here</a>. And someplace - why not here - I should mention that Ms. Hunter is a friend of mine, just so you don't think I'm being all objective or anything.
    </div>
    </div>

