    <h3 class="post-title">
	 
	 A Fair(y) Use Tale
	 
    </h3>
    

	         <div class="post-body">
	<div>
      Howdy!<br /><br />This is phenomenal.<br /><br /><object width="425" height="350"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/CJn_jC4FNDo"></param><param name="wmode" value="transparent"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/CJn_jC4FNDo" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" width="425" height="350"></embed></object><br /><br />Although Canadian Copyright law is different from that in the United States. - Thanks to <a href="http://museumblogthesis.blogspot.com/">Lynn Bethke</a> for pointing it out.
    </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Begin Feedburner FeedFlare -->
    <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;font-size:78%;font-family: arial;"><script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/blogspot/wjBk?i=http://www.zekesgallery.blogspot.in/2007/05/fairy-use-tale.html" type="text/javascript"></script></script></span>
    <!-- End Feedburner FeedFlare -->

    <p class="post-footer">
      <em>posted by Zeke's, the Montreal Art Gallery on <a href="http://www.zekesgallery.blogspot.in/2007/05/fairy-use-tale.html" title="permanent link">19.5.07</a></em><br>
      
